<task id="015" project="sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix">
  <metadata>
    <title>Reflection-load dynamic probe (instrument Program.cs localhost flag)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent (developer)</assigned>
    <tags>bff-api, inventory, reflection, instrumentation, phase-1</tags>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Requires code instrumentation in Program.cs; sequential</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add a localhost-only diagnostic flag to `Program.cs` that logs `AppDomain.CurrentDomain.GetAssemblies()`
    after `app.Build()` completes. Capture the dynamic assembly load list and commit to inventory/.
    This is the COMPLEMENT to task 014's static analysis — catches packages used via reflection
    (Graph SDK, Identity.Web, EF, MEL processors, config binding, DI string types).

    Critical: the instrumentation must be REVERSIBLE (single-purpose commit; revert after baseline
    captured) and must NOT activate outside localhost.
  </prompt>

  <role>.NET developer experienced with assembly resolution and DI internals.</role>

  <goal>
    File `inventory/reflection-probe.txt` containing the assembly list captured at localhost startup.
    The instrumenting commit MUST be revertible (no other behavioral changes).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="program">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
    <file purpose="claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="design.md §6 Phase 1 step 8">Instrumentation localhost-only; revert after capture</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Minimal API only; no Functions</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — do NOT add new registrations</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md">No new endpoints/services/DI without justification</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Phase 4 removal decisions for MEDIUM/HIGH tier depend on knowing what reflection-loaded
      code uses a package. Static grep misses these. The dynamic probe captures the actual
      runtime load list. Baseline (this task) and post-Phase-4 (per-candidate verification) must
      match — or differences must be accounted for. Revertibility matters because the diagnostic
      adds a code path even if it's localhost-only.
    </background>
    <dependencies><dependency task="008" status="not-started">Phase 0 gate</dependency></dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read current Program.cs to understand startup flow</step>
    <step order="2">Add diagnostic block: `if (app.Environment.IsDevelopment() &amp;&amp; Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("BFF_REFLECTION_PROBE") == "1") { ... }` that writes assembly list to stdout</step>
    <step order="3">Build + run locally with `BFF_REFLECTION_PROBE=1`</step>
    <step order="4">Capture stdout to `inventory/reflection-probe.txt`</step>
    <step order="5">Revert the Program.cs instrumentation in a separate commit; verify diff is clean</step>
    <step order="6">Update TASK-INDEX.md status</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">build + run</tool>
    <tool name="git">two commits: add, then revert</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="report">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/inventory/reflection-probe.txt</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs (changed then reverted)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">reflection-probe.txt contains assembly list (≥ 100 entries expected)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Program.cs has no instrumentation residue after revert (diff vs Phase 0 baseline is empty)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Diagnostic flag is localhost+env-var-gated (cannot fire in prod)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
